            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1602142344,
            "creation_date": 1602142344,
            "body": "<p>Yes its not the same. Multicast EIP is a way of sending a message to N recipients at the same time (where the number of recipient is fixed/known ahead of time).<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 64257783,
            "question_id": 64257638
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6146bee4895d4efc903c4dc4018de3bd?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 3398941,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2851729,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2851729/user2851729",
                "reputation": 183,
                "display_name": "user2851729"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1602142625,
            "creation_date": 1602142625,
            "body": "<p>yes, you correctly understand that there is difference between network layer multicast and apache camel multicast.<\/p>\n<p>The use case for camel multicast is when you want to send <strong>same<\/strong> message to the multiple endpoints. So in example from docs:<\/p>\n<p><code>from(&quot;direct:a&quot;).multicast().to(&quot;direct:x&quot;, &quot;direct:y&quot;, &quot;direct:z&quot;);<\/code><\/p>\n<p>The <strong>same<\/strong> message from &quot;direct:a&quot; will be send to all three endpoints. And the number of &quot;destination&quot; endpoints is defined for each route and could be different for different routes.<\/p>\n<p>Note that in case of:<\/p>\n<p><code>from(&quot;direct:a&quot;).to(&quot;direct:x&quot;).to(&quot;direct:y&quot;)<\/code><\/p>\n<p>You are chaining processing of the messages. The result from the &quot;direct:a&quot; will be send to &quot;direct:x&quot; and the result from &quot;direct:x&quot; will be send to &quot;direct:y&quot;, so &quot;direct:y&quot; could get different message as &quot;direct:x&quot;.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 64257848,
            "question_id": 64257638
        }
    ],
